-- Apple shares up after Jobs introduces mobile phone
-- 
-- Tue Jan 9, 2007 12:59pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/09/us-apple-shares-idUSN09524320070109

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Apple Computer Inc. rose as much as 3.4 percent on Tuesday after the iPod maker's chief executive, Steve Jobs, introduced the company's much-anticipated mobile phone. 

 Apple shares traded up 2.5 percent at $87.61 minutes after the initial rise. Jobs was speaking at the Macworld conference in San Francisco.